<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The {{request()}} method does not mind the adapter configuration once an adapter has been loaded. Consequent to this fact and the current API restrictions (non-public related class members), it seems impossible to change the adapter once an adapter is available.</p>

<p>A workaround is to create separate {{Zend_Http_Client}} objects for each adapter needed in a particular use case. (My particular use case is unit testing {{Zend_Service_Flickr}}.) The workaround is suboptimal because it requires management of an object for each different adapter, whereas the class could allow changing the adapter for a single {{Zend_Http_Client}} instance dynamically, throughout the instance's lifetime.</p>

<p>There are several ways in which this could be solved, but I would like to defer to Shahar for comment.</p>

